reviewText: The 1-2-3 Count with Me side is better and it has more engaging songs and it's funnier, even I enjoy it and my toddler and I have seen it many, many times. The other side wasn't as engaging, Perhaps it's best to order just one separately instead of together.
Title: Sesame Street Double Feature: 123 Count With Me/Learning About Letters

reviewText: My 2 year old nephew loves this! Great movie to help with abc's and numbers. And it's 2 for 1!
Title: Sesame Street Double Feature: 123 Count With Me/Learning About Letters

reviewText: My 2 boys, 2 and 3.5 years old didn't like these at all. They took stuff from the late 70's / early 80's for these dvd's. My 2 year old loves basically every dvd that has something to do with numbers or letters... but he never paid attention to these. So we gave these away after a couple weeks.
Title: Sesame Street Double Feature: 123 Count With Me/Learning About Letters

reviewText: My grandson has mild Autism, and he love to watch cartoons, but we make sure they are appropiate for him. This is a great learning tool.
summary: Also great for children with Autism
Title: Sesame Street Double Feature: 123 Count With Me/Learning About Letters

reviewText: The DVD was ok...it seem to have been very redundant and does not keep the interest very long.
Title: Sesame Street Double Feature: 123 Count With Me/Learning About Letters

reviewText: I loved this DVD.. my son played it over and over and over again.  I grew up watching Sesame Street, so this will always be a winner for me :)
Title: Sesame Street Double Feature: 123 Count With Me/Learning About Letters

reviewText: LOVE this DVD set!  It is FUN not just for the children, but for the parents, grandparents and daycare providers that you will find yourself singing, "1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6, that's how the numbers go....." as I do but my husband does as well!  I continue to purchase this DVD as gifts for all I know with toddlers.  I recommend this DVD to EVERYONE with children!
Title: Sesame Street Double Feature: 123 Count With Me/Learning About Letters

reviewText: My son who is four is learning how to count and loves counting with the sesame street crew. A great fun time for little ones.
Title: Sesame Street Double Feature: 123 Count With Me/Learning About Letters
